Quick tip for OSX users:<br /><br />If you're running Snow Leopard and have the latest Xcode tools installed, the latest version of GCC tries to build 64-bit by default which causes a run-time segmentation error with ASM6. Use the "-m32" option to force GCC to output a 32-bit version which works fine.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3896">neilbaldwin</a> — Sat Nov 14, 2009 3:44 am</p><hr />
